Text	In 1985 Lata Pada and her family decided to take an extended vacation to India .	On 23 June of that year Vishnu Pada and daughters Arti and Brinda died in the bombing of Air India Flight 182 .	Lata Pada was not aboard since she left on an earlier date to tour India for Bharatanatyam recitals in Bangalore and across India ; Lata was in Mumbai rehearsing for her tour , while her husband and daughters stayed behind in Sudbury , Ontario because Brinda was graduating from high school ; afterwards the three flew on Air India 182 .	Lata Pada became a spokesperson for the families of the victims .	Lata Pada expressed disappointment in the Canadian government 's investigation of the Air India incident .
